s](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/shared/error.rs#L19).\n- [x] The v1 CLI surface uses `clap` subcommand routing and the non-slice command groups are stubbed to fail non-zero with `\"not yet implemented\"` messaging: [cli/mod.rs](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/cli/mod.rs#L14), [config.rs](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/cli/config.rs#L19), and the parallel `project`, `run`, `requirements`, `daemon`, and `conformance` modules follow the same pattern.\n- [x] Required Gherkin coverage is seeded in [workspace_init.feature](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/conformance/features/workspace_init.feature#L1) and [flow_discovery.feature](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/conformance/features/flow_discovery.feature#L1).\n- [x] Required tests and verification are in place: [domain_test.rs](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/unit/domain_test.rs#L3), [workspace_test.rs](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/unit/workspace_test.rs#L8), and [cli.rs](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/cli.rs#L9); `cargo build`, `cargo test`, and `cargo clippy --all-targets --all-features -- -D warnings` all passed under the `nix` toolchain wrapper.\n\n## Notes\nNo concrete spec gaps, regressions, or maintainability issues stood out in the current `ralph-burning-rewrite` tree. I also spot-checked runtime behavior beyond the tests: `flow show docs_change` and `flow show ci_improvement` report `Final review enabled: no`, `config show` exits non-zero with `config show is not yet implemented`, and `init` writes a `workspace.toml` containing `version = 1` plus an RFC3339 `created_at` timestamp.\n\nThe provided implementation diff was empty, so this approval is based on the checked-in crate state rather than a patch delta.\n\n## Commit Message\nBootstrap slice 1 ralph-burning workspace init and flow discovery"}}
